guid><pubDate>Fri, 12 May 2023 05:08:02 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/110355380276669912</link><description>Dinner down Providence.&lt;br/&gt;Earl Miller, Michael Frank, Brad Postle, Theresa Desrochers, Chris Moore&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/355/380/348/629/629/original/a1a474710533f35c.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/355/380/348/629/629/original/a1a474710533f35c.jpg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110355380434975832</guid><pubDate>Fri, 12 May 2023 11:04:29 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Sepiedeh Keshavarzi</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@SepiKeshavarzi/110339290107938852</link><description>Exciting news! Keshavarzi lab is officially open at &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/CambridgeUni" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;CambridgeUni&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. We investigate the neural mechanisms underlying &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/selfmotion" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;selfmotion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/orientation" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;orientation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. have open positions for &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/Postdocs" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Postdocs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/PhD" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;PhD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; students &amp;amp; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/researchassistant" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;researchassistant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Visit our website to learn more about our work and available positions and contact us to apply. Job ads coming soon, but we are accepting applications now on a rolling basis. Help spread the word! &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/neurosciencejobs" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neurosciencejobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/postdocjobs" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;postdocjobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/PhDpositions" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;PhDpositions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://neuromatch.social/tags/ResearchJobs" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;ResearchJobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.keshavarzilab.com/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;keshavarzilab.com/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110355633026520194</guid><pubDate>Fri, 12 May 2023 12:08:46 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Gary Marcus</title><link>https://sigmoid.social/@garymarcus/110356640782366733</link><description>⚠️ @geoffreyhinton is worried; Yoshua Bengio is concerned, even &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://sigmoid.social/@sama" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;sama&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a little scared.The question is, what are we going to do about it? My TED talk is now live:&lt;a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/gary_marcus_the_urgent_risks_of_runaway_ai_and_what_to_do_about_them" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;ted.com/talks/gary_marcus_the_&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;urgent_risks_of_runaway_ai_and_what_to_do_about_them&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; @TEDTalks</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110356640881348752</guid><pubDate>Fri, 12 May 2023 16:25:03 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Andy Marfia 📸</title><link>https://universeodon.com/@andymarfia/110357988473011716</link><description>My one complaint with Mastodon is that I sometimes don't see very important local news as quickly as Twitter. For example, Chicago has a giant snapping turtle that we've named Chonk. &lt;a href="https://blockclubchicago.org/2023/05/12/chonk-an-enormous-snapping-turtle-on-the-chicago-river-is-stealing-citys-heart/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;blockclubchicago.org/2023/05/1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;2/chonk-an-enormous-snapping-turtle-on-the-chicago-river-is-stealing-citys-heart/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://universeodon.com/tags/Chicago" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Chicago&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://universeodon.com/tags/breakingnews" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;breakingnews&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://universeodon.com/tags/turtlenews" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;turtlenews&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110358676425045736</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 01:02:44 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Josh Simmons</title><link>https://josh.tel/@josh/110356837129007188</link><description>Hello, fellow US-based people. If you, like me, are alarmed at COVID tracking infrastructure being pulled offline, consider: &lt;a href="https://data.wastewaterscan.org/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;data.wastewaterscan.org/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Yes, it's more useful when in concert with other metrics, but we don't really have that 'luxury' anymore :blobcat_thisisfine: &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://josh.tel/tags/COVIDIsStillHere" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;COVIDIsStillHere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://josh.tel/tags/MaskUp" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;MaskUp&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://josh.tel/tags/USPol" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;USPol&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://josh.tel/tags/COVID" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;COVID&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110358689457914193</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 01:06:03 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Mackenzie Mathis 🦄</title><link>https://hachyderm.io/@TrackingActions/110360547933262478</link><description>🦓 Self-supervised multimodal ML is promising the next AI breakthrough - in our new work published in Nature, we debut &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/CEBRA" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;CEBRA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for self-supervised hypothesis- and discovery-driven science.📝 &lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06031-6" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nature.com/articles/s41586-023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-06031-6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;💻 &lt;a href="https://github.com/AdaptiveMotorControlLab/CEBRA" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;github.com/AdaptiveMotorContro&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;lLab/CEBRA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;🦓 &lt;a href="http://cebra.ai" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;http://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;cebra.ai&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Super excited about this work and more importantly so proud of my first PhD student &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://sigmoid.social/@stes" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;stes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (pictured!) and awesome masters student Jin Lee! 🦓🎊🖤✨&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/machinelearning" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;machinelearning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/EPFL" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;EPFL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/AI" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;AI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/360/547/971/495/664/original/cd3d2361d45462ee.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/360/547/971/495/664/original/cd3d2361d45462ee.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110360548127373461</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 08:58:41 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Quincy</title><link>https://chaos.social/@quincy/110354628646954640</link><description>Noah told the animals he'd saved: "go forth and multiply".And they did, but he noticed a couple of snakes just sitting in the corner, looking sad.And Noah asked them, "what's the matter"?They said: "sorry, we're adders. we can't multiply".Hearing that, Noah fetched his tools and a few planks from the ship and made them a wooden table:"Here, with a log table even adders can multiply."</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110361268911649146</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 12:02:02 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Steffen Schneider</title><link>https://sigmoid.social/@stes/110306878351883690</link><description>Beyond excited that CEBRA is out in Nature today: A new algorithm leveraging self-supervised and supervised contrastive learning for scientific discovery &amp;amp; hypothesis testing!📑&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-06031-6" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-060&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;31-6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;🦓 &lt;a href="https://cebra.ai" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;cebra.ai&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 🐤 &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/stes_io/status/1653873673634295812?s=20" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;twitter.com/stes_io/status/165&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;3873673634295812?s=20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110361783052303991</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 14:12:47 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Sarah Ruediger</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@sarahruediger/110362399794113674</link><description>Are you into 👀 visual processing? Then check out this brand new study on the function of tecto-thalamic inputs to higher areas in visual cortex 🧠 of 🐁. Hot off the press from the Scanziani lab. It was great fun to contribute to this project! Congratulations to the entire team! 👏🎉&lt;br/&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.cell.com/neuron/fulltext/S0896-6273(23)00307-0" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;cell.com/neuron/fulltext/S0896&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-6273(23)00307-0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/362/399/820/957/521/original/02c4c4d9ed19214b.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/362/399/820/957/521/original/02c4c4d9ed19214b.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110362578387356521</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 17:35:04 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Nicole Rust</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@NicoleCRust/110362018505851717</link><description>What if brain (dys)function is like weather?You've probably heard about the 1972 idea from Lorenz: A butterfly flapping its wings over Brazil causes a tornado it Texas. It's the idea that in a nonlinear system, small causes can lead to big effects. Note that for weather, we can forecast for a few days out given current conditions (because small causes take a while to have their big effects), but we don't really know the "causes" of the weather today at the level of butterfly wings.It seems likely that many of the causes of brain function and dysfunction will be like that as well - after all, the brain is unquestionably a complex nonlinear system.  Thus we might be able to forecast where a brain will be in the near term and we may be able to understand some of the principles that give rise to it's complexity. But the causes of an individual's brain dysfunction might never be clear.  (This is a pretty different way than most brain researchers think about things, I suspect).What does this imply for treatments?</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110363781264531560</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 22:40:56 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Mediagazer</title><link>https://mstdn.social/@Mediagazer/110357213237298897</link><description>Twitter appears to have been limiting search results for Bellingcat; Elon Musk has suggested that Bellingcat's mall shooting investigation was a "psyop" (Pete Syme/Insider)&lt;a href="https://www.businessinsider.com/twitter-appears-limit-bellingcat-after-elon-musk-called-it-psyop-2023-5?op=1" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;businessinsider.com/twitter-ap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;pears-limit-bellingcat-after-elon-musk-called-it-psyop-2023-5?op=1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://mediagazer.com/230512/p12#a230512p12" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;http://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;mediagazer.com/230512/p12#a230&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;512p12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110363843873513123</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 22:56:53 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Robert McNees</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@mcnees/110356189938199017</link><description>Florence Nightingale was born &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/OTD" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;OTD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in 1820.Though best known as a nurse (maybe a reductive and gendered way of siloing her contributions) she did pioneering work applying statistics to public health and communicating her results with innovative data visualization. Image: National Archives (UK)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/356/189/298/273/028/original/54d4d53c3220bfe7.jpeg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/356/189/298/273/028/original/54d4d53c3220bfe7.jpeg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/356/189/599/818/766/original/7d688b759790b5f2.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/356/189/599/818/766/original/7d688b759790b5f2.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110363854115222758</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2023 22:59:30 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Albert Cardona</title><link>https://mathstodon.xyz/@albertcardona/110363505152657669</link><description>Faculty position open at the &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/MRCLMB" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;MRCLMB&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in Cambridge, UK:Group Leader at the Neurobiology division: come join us!&lt;a href="https://www.jobs.ac.uk/job/CZP497/research-group-leader-neurobiology-lmb-2136" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;jobs.ac.uk/job/CZP497/research&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-group-leader-neurobiology-lmb-2136&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/academia" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;academia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/tags/jobs" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;jobs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110366533587381695</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 May 2023 10:20:55 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>katejjeffery</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@katejjeffery/110365734283015107</link><description>I'm looking for an RA to come and work with me in beautiful Scotland! Great cognitive neuroscience community here. 3-year post, rodent electrophys and imaging, with behaviour - details on jefferylab.com/ra-advert Closes May 25 - please could people boost 👍</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110366565551837529</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 May 2023 10:29:03 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Nicole Rust</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@NicoleCRust/110344950879071946</link><description>Curing the broken brain model of addictionIdeas about viewing addiction as a complex system are gaining traction, and they strike me as tremendously sensible (and a good path forward).  Here, addiction is viewed as emerging from the interactions of multiple biological, psychological and environmental causal influences. The research question then becomes: how do these influences interact and where can we best intervene?  It's described here:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0306460320307322" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;sciencedirect.com/science/arti&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;cle/pii/S0306460320307322&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;This position resolves some of the polarized debates between two extreme positions: &lt;br/&gt;1) the cause of addiction is a pathologically disordered brain &lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/nejmra1511480" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/nejm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ra1511480&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;2) the brain disease model of addiction is wrong.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41562-017-0055" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nature.com/articles/s41562-017&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-0055&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Parallel ideas are emerging in mental health:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/09637214221114089" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;77/09637214221114089&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Thoughts, insights or concerns?</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110366664584623375</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 May 2023 10:54:12 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Cheshire</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@magdelenehall/110366779975136760</link><description>Suella Braverman accused of breaching barristers’ code over ‘racist’ language&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/may/14/suella-braverman-accused-of-breaching-barristers-code-over-racist-language?CMP=Share_AndroidApp_Other" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;theguardian.com/politics/2023/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;may/14/suella-braverman-accused-of-breaching-barristers-code-over-racist-language?CMP=Share_AndroidApp_Other&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110367169509228223</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 May 2023 13:02:38 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Mikhail Popov</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@bearloga/110364107007714861</link><description>A difference of approximately one set of principles, one commitment to those principles, and one full length backbone.(Excerpt from &lt;a href="https://diff.wikimedia.org/2017/04/30/turkish-authorities-block-wikipedia/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;diff.wikimedia.org/2017/04/30/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;turkish-authorities